  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Architecture&amp;nbsp;Decisions Repository&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The architectural decisions (AD) repository contains all IT decisions that apply to the enterprise (or to business&#xD;
    domains, units, projects), the &quot;mandatory use of IPV6&quot; for example. Each AD contains the background and substantiating&#xD;
    information that was used to make the decision. When a new decision is added to the repository a notification is sent&#xD;
    out letting IT architects and other interested parties about the decision. See: &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../UAM/workproducts/uam_ad_repository_DE6DB3D6.html&quot; guid=&quot;_J8vp4MoDEdy25fQyv59CjQ&quot;>Artifact: Architectural&#xD;
    Decision Repository&lt;/a>.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Users are generally not interested in the background and substantiation, just the decision itself and&#xD;
    therefore&amp;nbsp;this &quot;Notification Report&quot; has been defined that provides a summary of the ADs with likes to the full AD&#xD;
    definition provided.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Notification Contents&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The &quot;notification&quot;&amp;nbsp;artifact extracts the decision portion of all ADs to be distributed in the notification,&#xD;
    providing a useful summary for IT architects and other stakeholders.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The rough contents of an Architecture Decision Notification are the &lt;em>title&lt;/em>, &lt;em>reference number&lt;/em>,&#xD;
    &lt;em>date,&lt;/em> &lt;em>description&lt;/em> and &lt;em>external reference&lt;/em> to the decisionâ€”consult the definition for more&#xD;
    detail.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
  <purpose>&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;a id=&quot;XE_Architectural_Decision__Notification&quot; name=&quot;XE_Architectural_Decision__Notification&quot;>&lt;/a>The Architectural&#xD;
    Decisions Notification artifact contains summaries of Architectural Decisions (AD) that are&#xD;
    &lt;strong>appro&lt;em>v&lt;/em>ed&lt;/strong> or &lt;strong>rejected&lt;/strong> for use within the enterprise IT architecture, domain&#xD;
    IT architecture, or other level of IT architecture. ADs are documented to:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Provide a single place to find important architectural decisions and to avoid unnecessary reconsideration of the&#xD;
        same issues;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Make explicit the rationale and justification of architectural decisions and IT architectures;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Alternatives are documented, including reasons why they were dismissed;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Ensure the architecture is extensible and can support an evolving system;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Provide a reference of documented decisions for new people who join the team;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Any decision involving IT hardware and software is included.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></purpose>
  <briefOutline>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The Architectural Decision Notification document&amp;nbsp;has just one repeated part for each included&amp;nbsp;AD. The&#xD;
    following&amp;nbsp;is extracted from each AD (also see:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../UAM/guidances/templates/uam_ad_summary_E8ECFBD8.html&quot; guid=&quot;_691yINWpEdyLINQdtlJihw&quot;>Template:&#xD;
    Architectural Decisions Summary Template&lt;/a>:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;blockquote style=&quot;MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;h3>&#xD;
        Architectural Decision&#xD;
    &lt;/h3>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        Describe the Architectural Decision. It is important to briefly state the context and scope of the Architectural&#xD;
        Decision. Use any figures or diagram to help the reader understanding the decision. The reader of this document&#xD;
        should understand the decision and its scope from this summary.&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;/blockquote>&#xD;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
    Optionally the following section of the architectural decision may be included for each AD in the summary:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;blockquote>&#xD;
    &lt;h4>&#xD;
        Implications&#xD;
    &lt;/h4>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        Document any implications of the decision, such as technology choice, cost, and support implications. Also document&#xD;
        and cross-reference any implications on other ADs, past or present.&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        The implications of the rationale have to be explored as well. Things such as:&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;ul>&#xD;
        &lt;li>&#xD;
            How will this Architectural Decision will be applied over time?&#xD;
        &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;li>&#xD;
            How will this Architectural Decision will be applied in multiple systems?&#xD;
        &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;li>&#xD;
            What are the skills requirements to support this Architectural Decision?&#xD;
        &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;li>&#xD;
            Have all stakeholders been involved in that Architectural Decision?&#xD;
        &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;/blockquote></briefOutline>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:ArtifactDescription>
